&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/critical-theory/domains/anarchism/domains/anarcho-nihilism/terms/hope/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/critical-theory/domains/anarchism/domains/anarcho-nihilism/terms/hope/> ;
  schema:name "Hope" ;
  schema:description "Anarcho-nihilism's analysis of hope as a political requirement — the demand that resistance justify itself through the expectation of a better future, which functions as a gatekeeping mechanism that excludes the honest, the traumatized, and the clear-eyed, and renders resistance dependent on a psychological state the existing order systematically undermines." ;
